Technology Brief -- International Business Machines:
   Computer Firm Cuts Prices
   10% to 16% on Some PCs
An IBM spokesman said the reductions reflect competitive
pricing in the industry. He said IBM regularly surveys the
computer market and adjusts its prices to stay competitive
with other computer makers.
   Separately, IBM confirmed that it began shipping its new
386SLC microprocessor, which upgrades the company's Personal
System/2(a) Model 57 SX. The 386SLC processor is a faster
version of the 386SX microprocessor.